CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Natural Resources – Recreational Striped Bass Catch Fishery Data Collection
3 Program – Reporting Established
4 FOR the purpose of requiring every person who catches striped bass under a Chesapeake
5 Bay and coastal sport fishing license or registration to report the catch to the
6 Department of Natural Resources; requiring establishing the Recreational Fishery
7 Data Collection Program in the Department to adopt regulations to carry out this
8 Act, including regulations authorizing certain reporting methods, authorizing a
9 person to report the catch through a mobile application to the maximum extent
10 feasible, and establishing a reporting method that is usable by persons who do not
11 have Internet access of Natural Resources to develop and implement a data collection
12 system for recreational anglers in the State; and generally relating to reporting
13 requirements for the recreational catching of striped bass the Recreational Fishery
14 Data Collection Program.
15 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
16 Article – Natural Resources
17 Section 4–745(a)(1) and (f)
18 Annotated Code of Maryland
19 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
20 BY adding to
21 Article – Natural Resources
22 Section 4–745(g)
23 Annotated Code of Maryland
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
