2 SENATE BILL 559
1 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
2 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
3 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
4 (a) In this section, “Program” means the Recreational Fishery Data Collection
5 Program.
6 (b) On or before December 31, 2026, the Department of Natural Resources shall
7 establish the Recreational Fishery Data Collection Program.
8 (c) The purpose of the Program is to develop and implement a data collection
9 system for recreational anglers in the State.
10 (d) In coordination with State and federal partners, the Department of Natural
11 Resources shall:
12 (1) survey and collect data on recreational fishing reporting programs in
13 other states; and
14 (2) subject to available funding, enter into a contract for the development
15 and implementation of a data collection system for recreational anglers.
16 (e) On or before December 31, 2027, the Department of Natural Resources shall
17 report to the Senate Committee on Education, Energy, and the Environment and the House
18 Environment and Transportation Committee, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the State
19 Government Article, on the findings of the Program, including a workplan detailing the
20 proposed development and implementation of a data collection system for recreational
21 anglers.
22 Article – Natural Resources
23 4–745.
24 (a) (1) Except as provided in subsections (c) and (d) of this section and § 4–217
25 of this title, a person may not fish for finfish in the Chesapeake Bay or in its tributaries up
26 to tidal boundaries or in State waters of the Atlantic Ocean and the Atlantic coastal bays
27 and their tributaries without first obtaining a Chesapeake Bay and coastal sport fishing
28 license or registration issued under subsection (d)(3) of this section and possessing the
29 license or registration.
30 (f) Every person licensed under this section shall submit any report the
31 Department requires in accordance with Department regulations.
32 (G) (1) EVERY PERSON WHO CATCHES STRIPED BASS UNDER A
33 CHESAPEAKE BAY AND COASTAL SPORT FISHING LICENSE OR REGISTRATION SHALL
34 REPORT THE CATCH TO THE DEPARTMENT.

SENATE BILL 559 3
1 (2) (I) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ADOPT REGULATIONS TO CARRY
2 OUT THIS SUBSECTION.
3 (II) REGULATIONS ADOPTED UNDER THIS PARAGRAPH SHALL:
4 1. AUTHORIZE REPORTING METHODS THAT THE
5 DEPARTMENT DETERMINES TO BE FEASIBLE;
6 2. TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT FEASIBLE, AUTHORIZE A
7 PERSON TO REPORT THE CATCH THROUGH A MOBILE APPLICATION; AND
8 3. ESTABLISH A REPORTING METHOD THAT IS USABLE
9 BY PERSONS WHO DO NOT HAVE INTERNET ACCESS.
10 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
11 January July 1, 2027. 2026. It shall remain effective for a period of 1 year and 6 months
12 and, at the end of December 31, 2027, this Act, with no further action required by the
13 General Assembly, shall be abrogated and of no further force and effect.
Approved:
